==English==
===Etymology===
[[Early Modern English]]; used at least 150 times by William Shakespeare.  Also used in [[Middle English]] by writer Geoffrey Chaucer, "me thinketh," and in [[Old English]] by the Beowulf poet, "me thincth."

In [[Middle English]] it was two words: the [[verb]] "thinketh" and the [[dative]] "me."

thinketh: it seems<br>
me: to me

=== Verb ===
'''methinks'''

# {{archaic}} It [[seem]]s to me.

